# Creating and working with custom fields

[!include [banner](includes/banner.md)]

Custom fields in Core HR can be added to pages within the application. For more ifnormation on how to create custom fields in Core HR, visit this this topic: 
[Create and work with custom fields] (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dynamics365/unified-operations/fin-and-ops/get-started/user-defined-fields)

The following CCDS for Apps entities now support custom fields created in Core HR:

- Worker
- Department
- Ethnic Origin
- Veteran Status
- Language code
- Job
- Job type
- Job function
- Position
- Position type

# Enabling custom fields to be used in CDS for Apps

Custom fields created in Core HR need to be enabled for them to be available for use in CDS for Apps. 

Follow these steps to expose a custom field on CDS for Apps data entity:

1. Select the custom field on the **Custom fields** form.
2. Expand the **Entities** section to view the set of relevant entities.
3. Click the **Edit** button.
4. Modify the **Enabled** field to be selected for each entity that should expose this field. CDS entities will have the prefix of cdm_. 
5. Click **Apply changes** to save your selections.

